# Backend patterns

- Java 21, Spring Boot 3.3; prefer existing packages under `com.migration.*`.
- Trust boundaries: validate at controllers; never log secrets or decrypted passwords.
- Config: env for secrets (JWT, encryption, OAuth); DB `app_config` for runtime tunables.
- Connectors: JAR SPI only — no `new PostgresqlConnectorPlugin()` in worker/API.
- Persistence: JPA entities in `packages/domain`; Flyway only in API (`ddl-auto: validate`).
- Tests: smallest failing unit/IT that proves the bug; no unbounded `findAll` in new APIs — page with `page`/`size`.
- Errors: fail closed on auth; use existing exception advice / GSpace hooks without duplicating notifiers.
